==回收残骸==
在{{link-en|东得克萨斯|East Texas}}、西路易斯安那和阿肯色西南部分县找到了包括人类遗体在内的超过两千件残骸。大部分残骸散落在了[[纳科多奇斯_(得克萨斯州)|纳科多奇斯]]到达拉斯西南的人烟稀少的地区。[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]报道说搜救队发现了包括手臂、足、躯干、心脏在内的人类遗体。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/1420965/Searchers-stumble-on-human-remains.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first1=Toby | last1=Harnden | title=Searchers stumble on human remains | date=2003-02-03 | access-date=2012-08-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908005642/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/1420965/Searchers-stumble-on-human-remains.html | archive-date=2017-09-08 | dead-url=no }}</ref>在事故发生后的数月内，人们组织起了最大的地面搜索。<ref name="News Researcher">{{cite web |url=http://researchernews.larc.nasa.gov/archives/2003/050903/Search.html |title=In Search Of... |accessdate=2009-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090320232815/http://researchernews.larc.nasa.gov/archives/2003/050903/Search.html |archive-date=2009-03-20 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> NASA发出警告说任何残骸都可能含有有害化学品，人们不应接触任何残骸并应向当地[[灾难应对|灾难应对]]部门或政府当局汇报其位置；任何人擅自占有残骸还将被起诉。由于残骸散布面积之广，[[业余无线电|业余无线电]]操作员们自发向搜索队提供通讯支持。<ref>{{cite web | author=awextra@arrl.org | title=''Hams Aid Columbia Debris Search in Western States'' | publisher=American Radio Relay League, Inc. | year=2003 | url=http://www.arrl.org/news/stories/2003/02/26/2/?nc=1 | accessdate=2007-02-01 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051104131736/http://www.arrl.org/news/stories/2003/02/26/2/?nc=1 | archivedate=2005-11-04 | deadurl=yes }}</ref>

一些装有[[秀丽隐杆线虫|秀丽隐杆线虫]]成虫（约1毫米长）[[培养皿|培养皿]]的铝制容器在事故后几周内被发现，这些线虫在再入与坠落时幸存<ref>{{cite web| author=Szewczyk, Nathaniel, et al.| title=''Caenorhabditis elegans'' Survives Atmospheric Breakup of STS-107, Space Shuttle Columbia| publisher=Mary Ann Liebert, Astrobiology| year=2005| url=http://www.liebertpub.com/prdetails.aspx?pr_id=428| accessdate=2006-11-02| archive-date=2012-05-29| archive-url=https://archive.is/20120529141120/http://www.liebertpub.com/prdetails.aspx?pr_id=428| dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title=Worms survived Columbia disaster| publisher=BBC News| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/2992123.stm| date=2003-05-01| accessdate=2005-12-16| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051106233827/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/2992123.stm| archive-date=2005-11-06| dead-url=no}}</ref>；2003年4月28日，这些培养物被确认仍然存活。<ref>[http://www.cmu.edu/magazine/03fall/wormsurvive.html Worms Survive Shuttle Disaster] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cmu.edu/magazine/03fall/wormsurvive.html |date=20120414105622 }} Fall 2003</ref>这些线虫是研究失重对[[生理学|生理]]影响的生物实验的一部分，由{{link-en|卡西·康利|Cassie Conley}}主持进行。

在搜索残骸时发生了一起直升机坠机事故，残骸搜索飞行员小朱尔斯·F·米尔和碎片搜索航空专家查尔斯·克热内克遇难，另外三人也因此受伤。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/STS107-N175PA.htm |title=The 'Columbia' Debris Recovery Helo Crash |publisher=Check-Six.com |accessdate=2009-09-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123171943/http://check-six.com/Crash_Sites/STS107-N175PA.htm |archive-date=2009-01-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

一些得克萨斯州居民找到了部分残骸，并无视警告、企图在[[网上拍卖|网上拍卖網站]][[eBay|eBay]]上以10000美元起价拍卖这些残骸。此拍卖被迅速移除，有关哥伦比亚号的节目、照片、贴布绣等商品在事故后迅速升值；与哥伦比亚号有关的商品数量也同时激增。<ref>{{cite news| title=Shuttle debris offered online| publisher=BBC News| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/2720225.stm| date=2003-02-03| accessdate=2007-05-27| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060923052013/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/2720225.stm| archive-date=2006-09-23| dead-url=no}}</ref>为回收被非法占有残骸开出的三天特赦期间，数百件航天飞机残骸被上缴。<ref>{{cite news| title=Debris Amnesty Ends, 9 May Face Looting Charges| agency=Associated Press| url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1454&dat=20030209&id=-2o0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=jR8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=5501,2583517| date=2003-02-08| accessdate=2012-08-27| archive-date=2021-02-04| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204124421/https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1454&dat=20030209&id=-2o0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=jR8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=5501,2583517| dead-url=no}}</ref>超过四万件找到的残骸无法辨识。最大的碎片包括前起落架轮胎<ref>{{cite news| title=Divers Find Shuttle's Front Landing Gear| publisher=Fox News| url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,78993,00.html| date=2003-02-19| accessdate=2010-04-25| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203053231/http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,78993,00.html| archive-date=2010-12-03| dead-url=yes}}</ref>和窗框。<ref>{{cite news| title=NASA begins packing up shuttle debris for storage|work=USA Today | url=http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2003-09-10-space-shuttle-storage_x.htm| date=2003-09-10| accessdate=2009-06-22}}</ref>

2008年5月9日，据报道哥伦比亚号上的一个硬盘上的数据被在事故中幸存。<ref>{{cite web |last=Fonseca |first=Brian |url=http://www.computerworld.com/action/article.do?command=viewArticleBasic&articleId=9083718 |title=Shuttle Columbia's hard drive data recovered from crash site |publisher=Computerworld.com |date=2008-05-07 |accessdate=2009-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090421084840/http://www.computerworld.com/action/article.do?command=viewArticleBasic&articleId=9083718 |archivedate=2009-04-21 }}</ref>该硬盘用于存储关于[[剪切稀化|剪切稀化]]性质的实验数据。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/25apr_cvx2.htm |title=The Physics of Whipped Cream |publisher=Science.nasa.gov |accessdate=2009-09-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901032246/http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/25apr_cvx2.htm |archivedate=2009-09-01 }}</ref>尽管这个340MB的硬盘部分受损，但是存储实验数据的部分安然无恙并得以恢复。

2011年7月29日，纳科多奇斯当局通知NASA说在一湖中发现了直径{{convert|4|ft|m}}的残骸。NASA鉴定此残骸为电力反应剂储存和分配系统的一部分。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/US/08/02/texas.shuttle.debris/index.html |title=Space shuttle Columbia part found in East Texas |publisher=CNN |date=2011-08-02 |accessdate=2011-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110802170346/http://www.cnn.com/2011/US/08/02/texas.shuttle.debris/index.html |archive-date=2011-08-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

哥伦比亚号的所有残骸存储于[[航天器裝配大樓|航天器裝配大樓]]闲置的办公用地中。所有机组成员遗体被另外存储于大楼专门隔间中。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.latimes.com/2004/jan/31/nation/na-remains31 | work=Los Angeles Times | title=Shuttle Columbia's Debris on View at NASA Facility | date=2004-01-31 | access-date=2012-08-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015153602/http://articles.latimes.com/2004/jan/31/nation/na-remains31 | archive-date=2012-10-15 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==纪念==
2003年2月4日，[[乔治·W·布什|乔治·W·布什]]总统同夫人[[劳拉·布什|劳拉]]在[[林顿·约翰逊太空中心|林顿·约翰逊太空中心]]为宇航员家属主持了追悼会。两天后，副总统[[迪克·切尼|迪克·切尼]]同夫人[[琳恩·切尼|琳恩]]在[[华盛顿国家座堂|华盛顿国家座堂]]的类似追悼活动中与华盛顿官员和全国一起致敬。是次追悼会上，歌手[[帕蒂·拉贝里|帕蒂·拉贝里]]演唱了''Way Up There''。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0302/06/se.03.html|title=CNN LIVE EVENT/SPECIAL: Remembering the Columbia 7: Washington National Cathedral Memorial for Astronauts|date=2003-02-06|accessdate=2011-09-15|work=CNN.com|publisher=CNN|first=Judy|last=Woodruff|authorlink=Judy Woodruff|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113193826/http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0302/06/se.03.html|archive-date=2012-01-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>

